div1.p:
Received a copy of the within Return this 22 day of July 1915
Attorney for Petitioner
IN THE DISTRICT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON Northern DIVISION.
In the Matter of the Application of LEWIS JOHNSON, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
FILED IN THE U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, NORTHERN DIVISION JUL 22 1915 FRANK L. CROSBY, Clerk, By Emd Deputy 2x
United States District Court for the Western District of Washington In the Matter of the Application of Lewis Johnson for Writ of Habeas Corpus

To the Clerk of the above Entitled Court: You will please enter our appearance as attorneys for Lewis Johnson in the above entitled cause, and service of all subsequent papers, except writs and process, may be made upon said Lewis Johnson, by leaving the same with
Geo R. Tennant & Hammond Office Address Mutual Life Bldg Seattle
NOTICE-Attorneys will please endorse their own Filings. Rule 11.
